Dia. 02 Step pae
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
{\colortbl ;\red255\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par White 1 has a plan.
\par After the exchange of Black 2 for White 3, if Black blocks at 4, White takes at 5 and resists with pae.
\par
\par However the four Black \'a1\'e3 stones have three liberties, therefore this is \cf1\b very unfavorable pae\cf0\b0  for White. (It is step pae)
\par
\par Therefore this variation is also a \cf1\b failure for White\cf0\b0 .
\par
\par }
